glue /ɡluː/

(gluing,glued,glues) 

1. N-MASS Glue is a sticky substance used for joining things together, often for repairing broken things. 胶; 胶水 

例： ...a tube of glue. …一管胶水。 

2. V-T If you glue one object to another, you stick them together using glue. 用胶粘 

例： Glue the fabric around the window. 用胶把这布粘在窗户四周。 

例： The material is cut and glued in place. 材料被剪开并粘到合适的位置。 

3. V-T PASSIVE If you say that someone is glued to something, you mean that they are giving it all their attention. 使全神贯注 

例： They are all glued to the Olympic Games. 他们都全神贯注于奥运会。

